*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]" {{C|by [[Tsuneo Sanda]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Hugh Quarshie: The Quarshie Quotient]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Episode I's mercurial Captain Panaka tells Scott Chernoff why acting in a ''Star Wars'' prequel beats Shakespeare any day.</small>
*"[[LucasArts: Behind the Magic]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*:<small>The release of the "lost" Biggs scenes and cut Cantina footage are just two highlights of LucasArts' new [[Star Wars: Behind the Magic|Behind the Magic]] CD-ROM. Jamie Painter peeks behind the curtain.</small>
*"[[Atari Wars: A Star Wars Video Game History|Atari Wars: A ''Star Wars'' Video Game History]]" {{C|by [[Matt Yeo]] and [[David Kelsall]]}}
*:<small>Before LucasArts, there was Atari and Intellivision. Matt Yeo and David Kelsall of the U.K.'s ''[[Star Wars: The Official Magazine]]'' lead this trip down ''Star Wars'' gaming's memory lane.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Rocks!|''Star Wars'' Rocks!]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>From rock and rap to country and reggae, ''Star Wars'' has inspired musicians of every genre. Jon Bradley Snyder unveils his exhaustive account of the best and most bizarre ''Star Wars'' music in the galaxy. And wev'e got the photos to prove it.</small>

